1784402682311204	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErIg		item.create	bn-qg0	{"description":"Deliver the versioned YAML schema and `campaign plan` command. Model frozen\ntargets/CIDRs, signaling and media ports, transports, credential references,\ncases, expectations, traffic ceilings, stop conditions, and evidence policy.\nResolution and validation must be side-effect free.\n\nAcceptance: invalid placeholders, empty scope, DNS results outside approved\nnetworks, unsupported combinations, missing ceilings, and arithmetic overflow\nfail before traffic. A deterministic plan states resolved destinations, every\ngenerated step, capture filter, exact hard maxima, and any assumptions. Include\nschema documentation, positive/negative fixtures, and tests proving command-line\noverrides can only reduce authorization.\n","kind":"task","labels":["campaign","safety","schema"],"parent":"bn-qsu","size":"m","title":"Specify the campaign manifest and fail-closed planner","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:FgkavCGnGqMyQ6CFstjX9oustaFS02IJ5oOGxtxTDOw
1784402682413784	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErIw		item.create	bn-2cg	{"description":"Implement the bounded process supervisor behind `campaign run`. Execute a\nfrozen plan with per-step and global deadlines, append versioned JSON events,\npropagate meaningful exit status, and own all child process groups.\n\nAcceptance: success, child failure, timeout, SIGINT, SIGTERM, and partial\nstartup follow deterministic state transitions. Cleanup is idempotent, stops\nnew traffic first, attempts graceful teardown within a bound, and leaves no\nchild or temporary network state. A loopback fake runner exercises crash and\ncancellation paths without network access. Event ordering and schema have\ngolden tests and bounded queues prevent untrusted tool output from exhausting\nmemory.\n","kind":"task","labels":["campaign","runtime","reliability"],"parent":"bn-qsu","size":"m","title":"Implement supervised campaign execution and structured events"}	blake3:pF5ZIF64itHJqXOk0mOICRo6OTOCBS-fLy0T5D9SHTs
1784402682517476	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErJA		item.create	bn-2ja	{"description":"Connect the runtime to existing capture, preflight, SIPp, report, and self-test\nprimitives. Create one collision-safe UTC run directory containing the frozen\nplan, timestamps, redacted commands, versions, logs, captures, and results.\nResolve secrets through environment/file-descriptor/provider contracts without\nplacing values in argv or persisted output.\n\nAcceptance: a one-call isolated campaign produces a complete run directory and\nreport; a failed preflight sends no call; capture starts before traffic and\nstops after bounded teardown. Tests scan argv, events, logs, and artifacts for\nfixture secrets. Existing standalone scripts remain backward compatible, and\nfile ownership works under rootless Podman.\n","kind":"task","labels":["campaign","integration","evidence"],"parent":"bn-qsu","size":"m","title":"Integrate capture, SIPp, secret references, and run directories"}	blake3:8oAwVvOKb8NobX58Z913Nk_EZCtFuqwZzwIWq9kmIVY
1784402682627886	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErJQ		item.create	bn-5pq	{"description":"Close the campaign-runner phase only after an independent acceptance suite\ndemonstrates fail-closed planning and reliable cleanup.\n\nGate: malformed and over-budget manifests emit zero packets; DNS scope is\nfrozen; Ctrl-C at every lifecycle state leaves no child, capture, qdisc, or\npartial mutable plan; fixture secrets never appear in process listings or\nartifacts; the loopback call succeeds; human and JSON errors are actionable;\ndocumentation covers authorization, dry-run review, secret delivery, and\nemergency stop. Record the test transcript and known limitations on the goal,\nthen manually close it.\n","kind":"task","labels":["campaign","exit-gate","quality","safety"],"parent":"bn-qsu","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: prove campaign safety and interruption recovery"}	blake3:rgaAEGSA1SoRqiXIMy09pk4zJflptYMcKCuom-nzuk4
1784402682737705	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErJg		item.create	bn-1ag	{"description":"Define internal records for frames, SIP messages, SDP revisions, RTP/RTCP\npackets, endpoints, and evidence references. Implement a narrow TShark\nfield/JSON adapter and the expectation/result JSON schemas with explicit\npass/fail/unknown semantics.\n\nAcceptance: parsing is independent of terminal formatting and locale; missing\nfields or unsupported encryption become typed unknowns rather than defaults.\nSchema versions and exit-code contracts are documented. Fixtures cover pcap\nand pcapng, IPv4/IPv6, truncated capture, malformed dissections, no-SIP, and\nno-RTP inputs. Authorization fields and payload bytes are absent from normal\nserialized records.\n","kind":"task","labels":["analysis","schema","tshark"],"parent":"bn-1da","size":"m","title":"Define typed packet records and a versioned assertion schema","urgency":"urgent"}	blake3:_T5--r3LQP_umOoDpSgHaVqS0un1fPwY06VOPMP66dA
1784402682858177	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErJw		item.create	bn-lt3	{"description":"Build the deterministic state model using Call-ID, tags, CSeq, Via branches,\nroutes, retransmissions, provisional/final responses, and offer/answer SDP.\nPreserve forks and ambiguity instead of forcing one linear call.\n\nAcceptance: fixtures reconstruct baseline, Digest challenge, retransmission,\nCANCEL, remote BYE, early media, fork, and re-INVITE/UPDATE flows. Each state\ntransition cites frame/time evidence. SDP revisions map media sections,\ndirections, addresses, ports, codecs, ptime, RTCP, and telephone-event payloads.\nIncomplete captures produce localized unknowns and never a complete-dialog\npass. Unit tests include deliberately colliding identifiers.\n","kind":"task","labels":["analysis","sip","sdp"],"parent":"bn-1da","size":"m","title":"Reconstruct SIP transactions, dialogs, and SDP media revisions"}	blake3:kbdEyUqo_zkrPuFCrcuDsnEckzrb9kwS09izKQGFk-U
1784402682976871	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErKA		item.create	bn-3e3	{"description":"Map negotiated media revisions to observed five-tuples, SSRCs, payload types,\nand RTCP reports. Implement assertions for directionality, expected endpoints,\ncodecs/DTMF, timing windows, sequence loss/duplication/reordering, jitter,\nunexpected transitions, media before answer, and media after teardown.\n\nAcceptance: every verdict reports evidence and applicability. One-way media,\nunexplained third-party addresses, payload mismatch, timestamp jumps, and\npost-BYE packets fail the relevant assertion. Legitimate renegotiation and\nsymmetric RTP are represented without false alarms. Metrics follow documented\nRTP/RTCP definitions and encrypted payloads receive transport-only analysis.\n","kind":"task","labels":["analysis","rtp","oracle"],"parent":"bn-1da","size":"m","title":"Correlate RTP/RTCP streams and evaluate call-path invariants"}	blake3:le2nlFagC4B7uwFRVphLLNIUyQPHTSngY1PYsbDsneM
1784402683135993	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErKQ		item.create	bn-39r	{"description":"Build a compact golden corpus and mutation suite that proves the oracle fails\nsafely. Include UDP/TCP signaling, IPv4/IPv6, early media, re-INVITE, fork,\npacket loss/reorder, DTMF, one-way media, unexpected endpoints, teardown leak,\ntruncation, and dissector disagreement.\n\nGate: human and JSON results agree; exit codes are stable; every expected\nfailure names frames and timestamps; unknown cannot satisfy required\nexpectations; repeated analysis is deterministic; large captures remain within\na documented memory/time envelope; no secret or decoded audio appears by\ndefault. Publish schema examples and manually close the goal only after the\nfull corpus passes.\n","kind":"task","labels":["analysis","exit-gate","fixtures","quality"],"parent":"bn-1da","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: validate the packet oracle against adversarial captures"}	blake3:QHJ99KpU8YP-_CxHWgs4h7brHOH4sDqUS4nNdhCVOsY
1784402683316377	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErKg		item.create	bn-sl8	{"description":"Create a seeded, source-generated canary containing direction-specific marker\nchirps/codes, calibrated silence, amplitude steps, and optional synthetic\nspeech. Produce PCMU, PCMA, and G.722 fixtures with a manifest of sample rate,\npacketization, expected marker positions, levels, and hashes.\n\nAcceptance: rebuilding is byte deterministic in the pinned image; assets are\ntiny and license-clean; directions cannot be confused; silence and clipping\nthresholds are documented; generated source rather than opaque binary blobs is\nauthoritative. Unit tests decode each asset and recover every expected marker.\n","kind":"task","labels":["media","fixtures","codecs"],"parent":"bn-3oz","size":"s","title":"Generate deterministic multi-codec audio canary assets"}	blake3:iFSU5sLPA00i_BeAfynMQ5ba_WYwYK9FUS4hOwD4c70
1784402683453396	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErKw		item.create	bn-1wv	{"description":"Integrate SIPp RTP streaming/PCAP play or a small packetizer to send negotiated\ncanary media. Add RFC 4733 event generation and validation using the negotiated\ndynamic payload type, clock, marker/end bits, duration progression, redundancy,\nand sequence behavior.\n\nAcceptance: an isolated echo fixture receives and returns both audio and a\nconfigured digit sequence. Unsupported codec/keying combinations fail before\nsending. Source/destination ports derive from current SDP, transitions after\nre-INVITE are bounded, packet timing is measured, and generated traffic exactly\nmatches a checked-in packet-level expectation.\n","kind":"task","labels":["media","rtp","dtmf"],"parent":"bn-3oz","size":"m","title":"Send canaries and standards-correct RFC 4733 events"}	blake3:wSuWoid-m2lKMqmgYwcvXrcRQ3SX1d0YwO-ddHDMKcQ
1784402683569561	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErLA		item.create	bn-1ai	{"description":"Implement correlation-based detection of canary markers and calibrated\nregions. Report acquisition time, round-trip latency, missing regions,\ndropouts, clipping, gross gain changes, duration drift, channel/direction swap,\nand unexpected energy during silence. Export typed facts into the assertion\nresult schema.\n\nAcceptance: results include uncertainty and packetization tolerance; no\none-way latency or MOS claim is made without the required instrumentation.\nUnsupported or encrypted payloads return not-measurable. Synthetic fixtures\nindependently vary delay, amplitude, clipping, silence, and loss to prove each\ndetector and avoid one metric masking another.\n","kind":"task","labels":["media","qoe","analysis"],"parent":"bn-3oz","size":"m","title":"Measure media continuity and round-trip marker latency"}	blake3:Mf5E4i-6mLg62-XGelKip7Y8dixKMCCawG8ulF3GjTY
1784402683786733	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErLQ		item.create	bn-3pf	{"description":"Validate the complete canary path over loopback and seeded delay, jitter,\nburst-loss, duplication, and reordering profiles.\n\nGate: clean loopback recovers every marker/digit; latency is within one\npacketization interval; injected faults cross only their documented\ntolerances; repeat runs remain within stated variance; one-way/all-zero/clipped\nmedia and malformed DTMF fail; decoded WAV remains opt-in and sensitivity\nlabeled. Record calibration results and known codec limits before manually\nclosing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["media","exit-gate","netem","quality"],"parent":"bn-3oz","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: calibrate the media oracle under seeded impairment"}	blake3:vENxKp6lha8y2PtOruNISiBQixAOPT-PzVbH6FLw_xg
1784402683910036	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErLg		item.create	bn-2gp	{"description":"Extend campaign manifests with finite factors for transport, address family,\ncodec/ptime, media protection, DTMF, early media, hold/re-INVITE, teardown\ninitiator, duration, NAT, and impairment. Add logical constraints, mandatory\ncases, selected interaction strength, and risk weights.\n\nAcceptance: parsing rejects empty domains, invalid values, contradictory\nconstraints, and unsupported factor references with useful diagnostics. A\nsatisfiability check explains a minimal conflicting constraint set. The sample\nFerivox model documents allowed and excluded combinations without probing a\nlive target.\n","kind":"task","labels":["coverage","schema","constraints"],"parent":"bn-2bt","size":"m","title":"Model matrix factors, constraints, and risk annotations"}	blake3:RTv_kZI4TrPVH9INHnucsTZxW7R61UG8LITk-fuWW5w
1784402684030535	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErLw		item.create	bn-3h6	{"description":"Implement or integrate a maintained covering-array generator with pairwise\ndefaults, constrained tuples, deterministic seeds, and variable strength for\nrisk-heavy factors. Add sequence-covering generation for ordered call actions.\n\nAcceptance: property tests enumerate every permitted t-way tuple and prove it\nappears, while forbidden tuples never appear. Output is stable for a seed,\ndifferent seeds preserve coverage, and a brute-force oracle validates small\nmodels. Sequence tests distinguish action ordering and constraints such as\nresume requiring a prior hold.\n","kind":"task","labels":["coverage","algorithm","combinatorial"],"parent":"bn-2bt","size":"m","title":"Implement deterministic covering and event-sequence generation"}	blake3:ZsN3FeJ765DowpRAqD95uR2xw0v7lOW8tsjcYIgnlb0
1784402684146029	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErMA		item.create	bn-1z5	{"description":"Convert generated rows/sequences into named runnable campaign cases. Combine\nmandatory cases, generated coverage, estimated traffic, historical failure\nhints, and risk ordering while preserving an auditable coverage ledger.\n\nAcceptance: every case passes campaign planning; aggregate maxima never exceed\nauthorization; truncation reports exactly which tuples remain uncovered; each\nresult maps back to factors and sequence positions. Markdown/JSON reports show\nCartesian size, executed size, achieved coverage, exclusions, seed, and no\nunsupported claim of exhaustive correctness.\n","kind":"task","labels":["coverage","campaign","reporting"],"parent":"bn-2bt","size":"m","title":"Compile generated matrices into budgeted campaign cases"}	blake3:FNBlkJhNd_lJE6-YdwhEhlJdfTBet6zuwoGdmX35B2U
1784402684343166	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErMQ		item.create	bn-ccj	{"description":"Exercise the matrix engine against random constrained models plus the Ferivox\nreference model.\n\nGate: all permitted pairs are covered, excluded pairs have reasons, the suite\nis materially smaller than the Cartesian product, deterministic regeneration\nworks, sequence ordering is covered, unsatisfiable models explain failure, and\nbudget truncation never reports full coverage. Generated cases must plan\nwithout traffic and the gate publishes size/coverage comparisons before the\ngoal is manually closed.\n","kind":"task","labels":["coverage","exit-gate","property-testing","quality"],"parent":"bn-2bt","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: prove compact coverage and honest truncation"}	blake3:tIQzTkwOFZgehoDxkT_yuoIUAw8G2eXg_im-LzrAkz4
1784402684531199	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErMg		item.create	bn-j8n	{"description":"Select one dialog from assertion records and classify local/remote roles,\ntransactions, timing windows, optional responses, SDP revisions, and teardown.\nCanonicalize Call-ID, tags, branches, CSeq, contacts, lengths, ports, SSRCs, and\ntimestamps into typed placeholders.\n\nAcceptance: baseline, challenge, CANCEL, remote-BYE, and re-INVITE fixtures\nyield stable intermediate models with provenance to source frames. Incomplete,\nambiguous, forked, or unsupported encrypted dialogs stop with explicit\ndiagnostics. Captured Authorization values and raw identities never enter the\nintermediate serialized model.\n","kind":"task","labels":["scenario","pcap","canonicalization"],"parent":"bn-1pf","size":"m","title":"Extract and canonicalize one captured SIP dialog"}	blake3:UYc-Bd4nXDfdRbuSXt1rc-F3_WplMclsk1dnIEoyuWs
1784402684644852	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErMw		item.create	bn-3jh	{"description":"Render the canonical dialog into annotated SIPp XML, injection CSV schema,\nexpectation YAML, media fixtures, provenance, and a README. Translate Digest\nchallenges into named secret references and generated authentication actions\nonly when semantics are understood.\n\nAcceptance: XML is syntactically linted, all waits have timeouts, dynamic\nvalues are regenerated, Content-Length/SDP addresses are correct, and the pack\ncannot target the captured peer without an explicit reviewed manifest. A field\ndisposition report lists kept, parameterized, removed, and unsupported values.\n","kind":"task","labels":["scenario","sipp","generation"],"parent":"bn-1pf","size":"m","title":"Generate a reviewable SIPp pack with safe authentication placeholders"}	blake3:BkTwjT2lLgdFNOMOkTHA0_TYcIZF9hbxL66og_wZ0Nk
1784402684754824	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErNA		item.create	bn-23n	{"description":"Run every generated pack against an isolated reference UAS/UAC, capture the\nresult, apply generated expectations, and compare canonical behavior with the\nsource dialog.\n\nAcceptance: validation requires zero external traffic, produces a focused\nsemantic diff, and fails on missing transaction, response-class change, wrong\nSDP, or teardown drift. Timing windows tolerate nondeterminism explicitly.\nSuccessful validation records image/tool versions and does not mark a pack as\nauthorized for staging.\n","kind":"task","labels":["scenario","validation","regression"],"parent":"bn-1pf","size":"m","title":"Validate learned packs offline and show semantic drift"}	blake3:MOopwt4m617lRljQ5ccPom3GQGyOMfcc_C_RPYLG47w
1784402684870822	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErNQ		item.create	bn-2id	{"description":"Run golden and hostile fixtures through extraction, generation, and offline\nvalidation.\n\nGate: supported single-dialog fixtures replay correctly; captured credentials,\nidentities, and third-party addresses do not appear; ambiguous/forked/truncated\ninputs emit no runnable pack; every generated path has a timeout; provenance\nremains traceable; and manual review instructions are clear. Attach secret-scan\nand packet-diff results before manually closing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["scenario","exit-gate","privacy","quality"],"parent":"bn-1pf","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: prove learned packs are private and fail closed"}	blake3:1QR7tGIXVrLi3TkihSQBbBYJnGULK6-VJuJPCE2XRgY
1784402685081022	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErNg		item.create	bn-ph5	{"description":"Implement deterministic collection of frozen plan, redacted commands, event\ntimeline, image/tool versions, captures, reports, assertions, stats, and notes.\nRecord hashes, media types, provenance, sizes, and sensitivity in a versioned\nmanifest.\n\nAcceptance: privacy lint detects fixture Authorization material, identifiers,\nunexpected networks, decoded audio, and oversized captures; high-risk content\nrequires explicit local override. Source artifacts are never modified. Repack\ndeterminism separates immutable content identity from creation metadata, and\nincomplete runs remain inspectable.\n","kind":"task","labels":["evidence","privacy","manifest"],"parent":"bn-2eu","size":"m","title":"Build evidence manifests, sensitivity classification, and privacy lint"}	blake3:NdGUht2-leBkqwwBJ5ZEMSwoa4dijJ6L99IWkybw5Lo
1784402685251896	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErNw		item.create	bn-15n	{"description":"Normalize nondeterministic SIP/RTP identifiers, ephemeral ports, and time\norigins, then compare dialogs, transitions, response timing, SDP, endpoint\ntopology, media metrics, and assertions between baseline and candidate packs.\n\nAcceptance: identifier-only changes compare equal; codec, endpoint, one-way\nmedia, setup latency, assertion, and post-BYE changes produce concise,\nevidence-linked diffs. Normalization rules are versioned and never erase\nsemantically relevant differences. Human, JSON, and JUnit views derive from\nthe same result model.\n","kind":"task","labels":["evidence","regression","diff"],"parent":"bn-2eu","size":"m","title":"Canonicalize and diff golden call behavior"}	blake3:9fdRTApX-05nD9wyi4DEtwrfFVxoB1PRTN-FlrBsr_Y
1784402685359296	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErOA		item.create	bn-30k	{"description":"Implement pack verification without the original workspace, optional minisign\nsignatures, recipient encryption, Markdown/JSON/JUnit export, and a minimal\nSBOM/image-digest record.\n\nAcceptance: verification rejects modified, missing, duplicate, traversal, and\nundeclared files; signature failure is distinct from content failure; encrypted\noutput never leaves plaintext temporaries after cleanup; CI export contains no\nhigh-risk artifact unless explicitly selected. Signing/encryption remain\noptional and keys are never managed by Sippycup.\n","kind":"task","labels":["evidence","supply-chain","ci"],"parent":"bn-2eu","size":"s","title":"Add offline verification, optional signing, encryption, and CI export"}	blake3:T71EL3fCL-Zp61ACx-KfdttKJ_0M1kbgY_6RGXR5Nec
1784402685466331	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErOQ		item.create	bn-3rf	{"description":"Validate packs with clean, secret-bearing, tampered, incomplete, and\ncross-machine fixtures.\n\nGate: clean packs verify offline; every byte/path tamper is detected; privacy\nviolations block default export; canonical diffs pass the equivalence and\nregression corpus; optional signatures/encryption interoperate with documented\ncommands; import requires no source workspace. Publish a sample sanitized pack\nand manually close the goal only after the gate passes.\n","kind":"task","labels":["evidence","exit-gate","privacy","quality"],"parent":"bn-2eu","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: tamper, privacy, and portability test the evidence pack"}	blake3:bThiUFOgY_Zw7jkXhDmgzWbSAFcCcpi1LAxToYv5olE
1784402685576288	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErOg		item.create	bn-2sv	{"description":"Design a Podman/network-namespace topology with explicit test, impairment, and\nuplink interfaces. Detect rootless/rootful, netem, IFB, classifier, and MTU\ncapabilities and render a no-change plan before mutation.\n\nAcceptance: the planner identifies ingress/egress direction honestly, rejects\nunsupported asymmetric cases, freezes target filters, snapshots host and\nnamespace routes/qdiscs, and requires a separately named dangerous mode for\nhost-network NET_ADMIN. Architecture docs include packet paths and privilege\nboundaries.\n","kind":"task","labels":["chaos","networking","safety"],"parent":"bn-lyg","size":"m","title":"Design the disposable topology and capability planner"}	blake3:Pz09SAjH1ESYUDr0E2FlooTZb0i3bf5pjoXIQ639E1g
1784402685688429	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErOw		item.create	bn-2et	{"description":"Implement reviewable profiles for clean, fixed delay, jitter/correlation,\nburst loss, constrained uplink, reorder, duplicate, MTU/fragmentation, and\nasymmetric media. Translate schema to netem/qdisc/filter commands.\n\nAcceptance: profiles have deterministic seeds where supported, bounded values,\nexplicit direction/duration, and frozen target selectors. Generated commands\nare unit tested and dry-run printable. Invalid percentages, impossible queue\ncombinations, missing delay for reorder, or unscoped profiles fail before any\nqdisc changes.\n","kind":"task","labels":["chaos","netem","profiles"],"parent":"bn-lyg","size":"m","title":"Implement seeded impairment profiles and target filters"}	blake3:1j-2H4-OjVn5RHw4D1VerEhUzuhHOO3JR9Gx2DGmXHg
1784402685799865	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErPA		item.create	bn-kpu	{"description":"Apply only planned namespace objects, tag every created object, clean them\nidempotently on all exits, and compare requested impairment with packet-level\nobservations.\n\nAcceptance: success, failure, SIGINT, killed child, and repeated runs restore\nthe exact pre-run state. Cleanup never deletes an object it did not create.\nReports show requested versus observed delay/loss/reorder within documented\nkernel tolerances and flag insufficient samples. Campaign cancellation stops\ntraffic before topology teardown.\n","kind":"task","labels":["chaos","reliability","measurement"],"parent":"bn-lyg","size":"m","title":"Own chaos lifecycle cleanup and measure observed impairment"}	blake3:fYqiFB5IZb0wyTRJ1jDtGTSljh-3mVYJ24T6hlUSD5o
1784402685910270	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErPQ		item.create	bn-1id	{"description":"Run capability, impairment, and failure-injection tests on a disposable test\nhost/CI runner.\n\nGate: default mode leaves host routes/qdiscs byte-identical; unrelated traffic\nis unmodified; target traffic experiences each supported profile; all injected\nlifecycle failures clean up; unsupported capabilities fail loudly; dangerous\nmode requires explicit dedicated-VM confirmation. Save before/after snapshots\nand observed distributions before manually closing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["chaos","exit-gate","safety","quality"],"parent":"bn-lyg","size":"s","title":"Exit gate: prove chaos never leaks onto the host"}	blake3:KeAAexNAWkhNoj1_y1PW4yooFZ4jvTkDwVKRXDmTnHg
1784402686016744	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErPg		item.create	bn-18q	{"description":"Build a provenance-tagged corpus beginning with RFC 4475 SIP messages and\nfocused media-plane cases. Each case records exact bytes, validity, required\ndialog state, risk, expected/acceptable outcomes, and traffic cost.\n\nAcceptance: cases cover length/header ambiguities, bounded extremes,\ntransaction/tag/CSeq anomalies, SDP contradictions, RTP sequence/timestamp/\nSSRC/payload transitions, RFC 4733 edge behavior, and malformed RTCP. A\nreference fixture verifies sent bytes. No case performs credential guessing,\nspoofed reflection, or unbounded amplification.\n","kind":"task","labels":["robustness","corpus","standards"],"parent":"bn-3ka","size":"m","title":"Curate bit-exact SIP, SDP, RTP, DTMF, and RTCP torture cases"}	blake3:_Y90NqUV_Nya37E4JcQyVW-mZVZDCr7XI1MIvcWpCzg
1784402686142892	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErPw		item.create	bn-1kk	{"description":"Establish the minimum dialog state, inject one selected case/mutation, classify\nthe response, and place a clean recovery canary before continuing. Enforce\nimmutable packet/byte/case/rate/concurrency/duration/failure ceilings.\n\nAcceptance: dry-run lists exact cases and maximum traffic; defaults are\nsingle-case and low-rate; operator stop, health callback, timeout threshold,\nserver-metric threshold, or failed recovery canary halts new cases\nimmediately. Captures preserve exact evidence and clean baseline traffic is\ndistinguishable from the mutation.\n","kind":"task","labels":["robustness","runtime","safety"],"parent":"bn-3ka","size":"m","title":"Implement the state-aware torture runner and recovery gate"}	blake3:R8PnoCoQyA2pPlkTzl3BVLgav9bcBxQq1awgFDuwOYw
1784402686249090	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErQA		item.create	bn-33h	{"description":"Implement hierarchical delta debugging over message sections, headers, values,\nbody lines, and mutation dimensions. Retest candidates with a configurable\nquorum while preserving original safety ceilings.\n\nAcceptance: composite fixture failures reduce to a smaller exact-byte\nreproducer with provenance and 3-of-5 stability by default; flaky outcomes are\nlabeled rather than over-minimized. Minimization cannot introduce new bytes,\ndestinations, states, or traffic above the source authorization. Save command,\ncapture frames, expected/actual outcome, and reduction trace.\n","kind":"task","labels":["robustness","minimization","reproducibility"],"parent":"bn-3ka","size":"m","title":"Minimize reproducible protocol failures into standalone cases"}	blake3:aXQ156Sk7VeY878p8Z1liUMhmIaqzqE05Z3sPU3CvBE
1784402686354842	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErQQ		item.create	bn-151	{"description":"Exercise the corpus against isolated tolerant and deliberately fragile\nreference endpoints with injected health failures.\n\nGate: every case sends bit-exact bounded traffic; expected outcomes classify\ncorrectly; recovery failure stops the suite; all hard ceilings hold under CLI\nattempts and minimization; a seeded composite failure shrinks reliably; no\ncredential/reflection/load behavior exists; evidence reproduces offline. Obtain\nexplicit owner review of default limits before manually closing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["robustness","exit-gate","security","quality"],"parent":"bn-3ka","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: validate torture safety, recovery, and minimization"}	blake3:GdH8VhyZ_uT_Bi8d-rBUG_u7h0Htt0-ngrc2P38dSBA
1784402686458851	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErQg		item.create	bn-1w3	{"description":"Extend the manifest with hard maxima for CPS, concurrent calls, media PPS,\ntotal calls, duration, hold time, cooldown, and recovery deadline. Implement\nlow-start step/ramp/hold control for one dimension at a time.\n\nAcceptance: command-line input can only lower maxima; integer/units overflow\nfails closed; plan computes worst-case traffic; pause/stop commands take\nprecedence over ramp events; no step starts without remaining budget. A\ndeterministic simulator verifies ramp timing and ceilings without network\ntraffic.\n","kind":"task","labels":["load","controller","safety"],"parent":"bn-1yq","size":"m","title":"Implement immutable envelope budgets and the ramp controller"}	blake3:YAa-Tb4OSZPV6AbNDCVo0dNE-y00426HgeZB06SjYUY
1784402686568214	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErQw		item.create	bn-224	{"description":"Consume SIPp rates/counters/latencies, packet-oracle results, RTP metrics,\nsocket errors, and optional bounded health adapters. Implement conservative\nrepeated-threshold/change-point logic with immediate hard-stop thresholds.\n\nAcceptance: adapters have deadlines and typed missing/stale states; no missing\nmetric becomes healthy. Synthetic traces cover stable, gradual, abrupt,\nhysteretic, noisy, and censored runs. The algorithm reports uncertainty and the\ntested knee interval, never an unobserved capacity point. Decisions cite the\nexact samples and configured policy.\n","kind":"task","labels":["load","analysis","statistics"],"parent":"bn-1yq","size":"m","title":"Fuse call/media observations and detect conservative degradation"}	blake3:R6Y8m2fv3e0UOdqujbViNDWby893UqyIHRGuOOP6JL4
1784402686675234	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErRA		item.create	bn-1m9	{"description":"On degradation, stop new calls, allow bounded teardown, cool down, and place\nperiodic one-call/media canaries until recovery or deadline. Produce a report\nof tested levels, triggers, uncertainty, hysteresis, recovery time, and\nauthorization-censored outcomes.\n\nAcceptance: baseline and post-load canaries use identical expectations; failure\nto recover is distinct from failure under load; teardown cannot extend the\nglobal deadline indefinitely; every ramp level maps to captures/assertions.\nSIGINT and adapter failure follow the same safe backoff path.\n","kind":"task","labels":["load","recovery","reporting"],"parent":"bn-1yq","size":"m","title":"Back off, prove recovery, and report the tested envelope"}	blake3:JIgBNlyrDh9PekoNVG5bWsLU7WTN9wKHGWe6k4OJ9Rs
1784402686781213	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErRQ		item.create	bn-1ax	{"description":"Test against synthetic endpoints that remain healthy, degrade gradually, fail\nabruptly, recover slowly, and never recover.\n\nGate: degradation triggers before hard maxima when evidence warrants; healthy\nruns stop exactly at the authorized ceiling; no run exceeds any traffic/time\nbudget; health loss stops immediately; recovery timing is correct; repeated\nseeded runs yield comparable intervals; reports never label untested traffic as\ncapacity. Attach test traces and owner-approved default policy before manually\nclosing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["load","exit-gate","resilience","quality"],"parent":"bn-1yq","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: stop safely at degradation and authorization ceilings"}	blake3:1CzlADJDtIrdj-Yc7i9Mu4s7DuyZ3298hFWFN-7wmoA
1784402686888424	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErRg		item.create	bn-1v6	{"description":"Define a bounded consumer of campaign/assertion events and a deterministic\nview-state reducer shared by interactive and noninteractive modes. Specify\nstates for planning, ready, running, warning, stopping, recovery, complete, and\nfailed.\n\nAcceptance: the UI never scrapes ANSI tool output; event schema mismatch and\ndropped/late events are visible; queues have backpressure; replaying an event\nfixture yields identical state. Non-TTY JSON exposes the same state and action\nsemantics. Architecture chooses a small maintained TUI dependency and keeps\nprotocol logic outside the UI.\n","kind":"task","labels":["tui","architecture","events"],"parent":"bn-2nj","size":"m","title":"Define the mission-control event and view-state architecture"}	blake3:4AnIn7wvT0qA-_xVGJKC3t_oqYyMkKoLvbfNE2ODKT8
1784402687001390	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErRw		item.create	bn-3gc	{"description":"Build pre-run and live panels for frozen authorization, warnings, planned\ncases, current/next step, UTC timing, remaining budgets, capture status/size,\nSIP ladder/counters, negotiated endpoints/codecs, per-direction RTP\npackets/loss/jitter, assertions, and recovery canary.\n\nAcceptance: layout remains legible at documented minimum size and resizes\nsafely; unknown/stale metrics are visually distinct from good; warnings link\nto evidence; first-run guidance explains when traffic starts and where output\nlives. Color is not the sole status signal and a one-key help overlay lists all\nactions.\n","kind":"task","labels":["tui","ux","observability"],"parent":"bn-2nj","size":"m","title":"Render scope, SIP ladder, RTP health, budgets, and guidance"}	blake3:2IVw0exUxhLM14C1jHjM5Qj_U76yZSL2JWMmpj-3dyY
1784402687108047	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErSA		item.create	bn-2o5	{"description":"Implement explicit start, pause-new-calls, graceful stop, emergency stop,\nskip, timestamped note/bookmark, and open-current-capture actions through the\ncampaign API. Integrate Termshark as a separate process without losing\nsupervisor ownership.\n\nAcceptance: stop is always available; dangerous actions require confirmation;\nrepeated keys are idempotent; remaining-budget display cannot exceed the\nsafety gate; notes are separate metadata included in evidence packs; Termshark\nexit returns to the same run state. No view rendering can initiate traffic.\n","kind":"task","labels":["tui","controls","evidence"],"parent":"bn-2nj","size":"m","title":"Add guarded controls, notes, bookmarks, and Termshark handoff"}	blake3:ma7_0yDWjjmlz8_TljOpyvG13QFLj5lrngZMFJipy4s
1784402687225793	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErSQ		item.create	bn-169	{"description":"Run snapshot, interaction, load, resize, and fault-injection tests plus a\nfirst-time-user loopback walkthrough.\n\nGate: a novice can plan, start one call, identify both directions, bookmark an\nevent, stop, and find the report using only in-app help; SIGINT/lost child/\nmalformed event/terminal resize/non-TTY paths preserve cleanup; bounded queues\nkeep input responsive under heavy tool output; screen-reader-friendly JSON is\ncomplete. Record the walkthrough and performance limits before manually\nclosing the goal.\n","kind":"task","labels":["tui","exit-gate","ux","quality"],"parent":"bn-2nj","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: usability, failure recovery, and responsiveness"}	blake3:2sRVIoFAHznbrRzZ0C_ECp9V3vwTj0A7EfSlecX2dXw
