1784411213270534	campaign_runtime	itc:v3:AWKfOZmeTnzMQAAAAAAAQb7tt677YAAAAAEsGQ		item.comment	bn-1z5	{"body":"Implemented matrix-to-campaign compilation in lib/sippycup/matrix_compile.py plus . It combines deterministic factor rows and action traces, preserves canonical generated row/sequence/factor/action annotations in every planned step, maps each row to an explicit literal AF/transport target, emits mandatory rows first, orders the rest by historical-failure then risk weight, derives capacity from authorized calls/packets/bytes/duration plus optional max-cases, rejects budgets that drop mandatory cases, and validates the exact generated manifest through compile_plan/source-lock/runtime contracts. JSON report v1 and Markdown include Cartesian/generated/selected sizes, seed, authorized/per-case/full/selected budget estimates, exact required tuple ledgers with coveredBy IDs, exact uncovered tuples, exclusions with reasons, action positions, history/risk scores, planned-not-executed state, and a non-exhaustive claim. Three CLI outputs are staged/linked atomically and refuse overwrite without partial siblings. Schema/docs/completion and the dual-stack/transport Ferivox sample were updated. Evidence: 5 compilation tests PASS; 58 focused campaign/matrix/covering/runtime tests PASS; full discovery 119 PASS; oracle 79 PASS; 20k benchmark 1.424724s and 3,942,782-byte peak PASS; compileall/bash -n/shellcheck PASS. Ferivox seed 19 full budget: Cartesian 590,490 -> 31 planned cases, 636/636 factor and 42/42 ordered tuples, totals 31 calls/124 packets/126,976 bytes/93s, zero network executions. Authorized sample: 4 cases, totals 4 calls/16 packets/16,384 bytes/12s, honestly incomplete at 242/636 factor and 22/42 ordered tuples. Known boundary documented: the basic SIPp adapter consumes destination transport/budget; other factor/action annotations require a scenario-capable adapter and packet evidence before claiming observed behavior."}	blake3:d7o_KwC5z1so85oe7g5ndDpb3kIE-K9JqKlytvGJvpM
1784411213322514	campaign_runtime	itc:v3:AWKfOZmeTnzMQAAAAAAAQb7tt677YAAAAAEsGg		item.move	bn-1z5	{"state":"done"}	blake3:UpSRX9lpfWqj7q7solCebbTswMV4xVUwKxBXDAwR9T4
1784411220230572	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErnwE		item.comment	bn-1wv	{"body":"Implemented bounded negotiated canary RTP sending and RFC 4733. Added sippycup media send, a strict media-session v1 schema/loader, completed-SDP-derived bind/destination endpoints and payload mappings, PCMU/PCMA/G722 packetization, dynamic telephone-event validation, RTP wire generation, real-time pacing, global wall deadline, byte-exact echo validation, timing/RTT reporting, re-INVITE revision transitions, and a packet/deadline-bounded echo fixture. RFC 4733 events use marker only on the first packet, fixed event timestamp, 160-tick duration progression to 800, three identical end packets, negotiated 8kHz clock/PT, and continuous sequence numbers. Unsupported codecs, SRTP/keying, mismatched SDP, unaligned revisions, missing DTMF mappings, or mutated assets fail before socket creation. Evidence: 11/11 focused tests pass; isolated UDP echo returns 50 audio plus 21 event packets for digits 12#, with send lateness and RTT within one 20ms interval and zero re-INVITE transition delay. Exact 71-packet golden plan passes, SHA-256 899798d56ce2762a11b007306a0225daabbe47bfde4f10faa5ba49bce079b2ff. Full root discovery passes 119 tests. Image 81f8837a864944c0ece961a14a16963c718b21c243b488dcbd9937f7bd118736 contains both media commands and reproduces the plan. Aggregate smoke reached both media commands; its only failure was the separately owned concurrent TUI binary missing from that pre-TUI-copy image, which root is rebuilding. No commit created."}	blake3:0gRc4c8wbzPUm8HfMmGwB0szwNFWRWjZ4gOOcyjcZxY
