1784413254869537	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErwAE		item.comment	bn-15n	{"body":"Implemented canonical golden behavior normalization/diff using learned canonical-model.json plus sippycup.results/v1 oracle-result.json. Added versioned sippycup.dev/golden-behavior-normalization/v1 boundary: typed SIP/RTP placeholders preserve equality relationships; raw SSRCs, high ephemeral ports, frame numbers, absolute evidence timestamps, and common transaction/media time origins normalize. Exact dialog/transaction order and responses, timing outside explicit tolerance, SDP/protocol/payload/codec/direction, well-known ports and oracle endpoint IPs, RTP packet payload behavior, streams/media metrics, assertions, completion, and teardown remain semantic; missing timing never equals numeric timing. Diff model is deterministic/path-sorted and every change carries baseline/candidate source evidence when available. Added concise category-aware handling for codec, topology, media direction/count, response timing, assertion, SDP, dialog, and post-BYE drift. Human, canonical JSON, and JUnit are pure renderers of the same result. Added sippycup-diff CLI (exit 0 equal, 1 different, 2 invalid), strict bounded pack loading, public JSON schema, docs/README, container and smoke wiring, and 7 dedicated mutation/equality tests (31 learned tests total). Final verification: full repository 165/165; oracle 79/79 plus 20k-packet benchmark; compile/schema parse; Podman rebuild e317fd41ac1c..., smoke includes sippycup-diff; in-container regenerated-call-ID equality returned zero changes. One earlier full run overlapped a concurrent chaos-topology edit and transiently failed; isolated rerun and two subsequent complete runs passed."}	blake3:jH3BsHPc3Omr9K6wS55-0QmuYhraHA_4VoqfTP6cGIE
