1784497886222599	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr1gI		item.comment	bn-1as	{"body":"Exit gate complete. Registry exposes 29 unique public commands; 17 dedicated CLI contract tests cover completeness, malformed/duplicate/symlink-safe registry handling, offline help, JSON/schema, typo suggestions, dry runs, fixed targets, direct/host/container routing, Podman/nerdctl/Docker resolver fakes, argv boundaries, legacy help, exit 23 and SIGTERM propagation, docs policy, completion, and version. strace observed zero network syscalls for every public COMMAND --help path. Full suite 306/306 passed in 72.531s; image 33317a0925c35f212843059d838ec42744886fd0fac69e09c7e5dc8ce57cb0d2 built and passed smoke; natural selftest/report/torture/doctor routes and read-only isolated chaos capabilities passed. No target traffic."}	blake3:zjyxTx55lbsi6A6HvANL4WZwWLBU9l2FfgRPDc2wzDc
1784497886245257	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr1wI		item.move	bn-1as	{"reason":"Unified CLI contract, safety, compatibility, documentation, full regression, real routing, image build, and smoke gates all pass.","state":"done"}	blake3:-rW05GgdVBLbGKgo2Wa6yXSWuJfKxI_uwGxhRRJzIi8
1784497886248973	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr2AI		item.move	bn-3kt	{"reason":"auto-completed: all children of bn-3kt are done","state":"done"}	blake3:NlYqd1ZGesGayDAZ2zjGFkOLQeXl3LufOVtCS31As_Y
1784499296237668	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr2QI		item.create	bn-mry	{"description":"Provide a lightweight Model Context Protocol control plane over Sippycup so local agents can discover documentation, schemas, capabilities, and deliberately allowlisted workflows. Begin with an offline stdio server and bounded read-only tools. Live target activity must remain separately gated by external authorization, immutable reviewed plans, hard ceilings, and complete audit evidence; never expose a generic shell or arbitrary command execution.","kind":"goal","labels":["mcp","agents","integration","security"],"parent":"bn-22t","size":"xl","title":"Expose Sippycup safely through MCP"}	blake3:i3Rmx8np9NRqU2kb33tVZcIMkX-BmAhT6k0R_qNmEnY
1784499304080920	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr2gI		item.create	bn-2oi	{"description":"Deliver a stdio-only MCP server that works through the unified Sippycup launcher with networking and packet capabilities removed. Publish a confined discovery surface and typed offline/read-only tools, produce bounded structured results, document client setup, and prove the server cannot initiate target traffic or escape its workspace.","kind":"goal","labels":["mcp","offline","security"],"parent":"bn-mry","size":"xl","title":"Phase 1: Ship the local offline MCP foundation"}	blake3:YngJn5wonx04h0hDxJxCBDK3ExJfky9aL7qYYge7FJw
1784499304257055	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr2wI		item.create	bn-1hq	{"description":"After the offline foundation is proven, expose narrowly scoped preparation, preflight, and one-call workflows. Bind every live request to an externally approved, unexpired target profile and reviewed artifact digest; require literal endpoints, hard ceilings, audit records, and fail-closed authorization checks. MCP must not contain an authorize operation.","kind":"goal","labels":["mcp","live","authorization"],"parent":"bn-mry","size":"xl","title":"Phase 2: Add approval-bound live MCP workflows"}	blake3:pUdDL8E6mvdwaFYzs4i9BUNczwckEi9Tr6MuKiOX9Ak
1784499304447879	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr3AI		item.create	bn-291	{"description":"Evaluate and, only where justified, implement supervised campaign lifecycle tools and authenticated remote MCP transport. Preserve cancellation, concurrency/rate ceilings, evidence completeness, least privilege, and per-client identity. Keep dangerous primitives such as arbitrary shell, unbounded scanners, raw packet recipes, chaos, credential attacks, and unrestricted load outside the MCP surface.","kind":"goal","labels":["mcp","campaigns","remote"],"parent":"bn-mry","size":"xl","title":"Phase 3: Add supervised campaigns and optional remote transport","urgency":"punt"}	blake3:hGEMrBd7tOF93zFXoKb-p5uL0drtnMeYP4a4UL7KNWw
1784499320906690	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr3QI		item.create	bn-371	{"description":"Document trust boundaries among the MCP client, local stdio server, container runtime, mounted work directory, Sippycup libraries, and external targets. Define the explicit Phase 1 resource/tool allowlist, data sensitivity and redaction rules, path and output bounds, protocol/version policy, and negative list. Acceptance: no generic shell, arbitrary argv, target-active operation, raw journal export, unrestricted file read, remote transport, or authorization mutation is reachable; decisions are testable and reflected in public documentation.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","security","architecture"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Specify the MCP threat model and allowlist contract"}	blake3:gqksACyiMrkl1AE1DXK9ok92wnA8wzhZ5oQorSQmcm4
1784499345790780	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr3gI		item.create	bn-7iz	{"description":"Add the official stable Python MCP SDK as an isolated/version-pinned optional runtime dependency, implement a stdio-only server entrypoint, expose it through the command registry and unified launcher, and provide actionable behavior when the optional dependency is absent. Keep protocol code behind a thin adapter so a future SDK major-version migration is localized. Acceptance: initialize, capability negotiation, shutdown, stderr logging, and clean EOF work with a stock MCP client while stdout remains protocol-only.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","packaging"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Package a version-pinned stdio MCP server"}	blake3:suncYQffjjFjFCLfvmmk1oe9t5Mz-i3vwHeeFlJR95w
1784499345976033	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr3wI		item.create	bn-w23	{"description":"Publish versioned command metadata plus deliberately selected public docs and JSON schemas as MCP resources. Resolve names through an allowlist, reject traversal and symlink escapes, enforce byte limits, and do not expose arbitrary repository files, raw assessment journals, credentials, captures, or run directories. Acceptance: agents can enumerate and read the safe catalog; malformed, encoded, oversized, and escaping identifiers fail without data disclosure.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","discovery","resources"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Expose a confined MCP discovery catalog"}	blake3:TxHvuQGR9tuozebztqU47wRq4UXaqsJ8ppFu7jl58lA
1784499346156268	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr4AI		item.create	bn-mtv	{"description":"Expose explicit typed adapters for safe offline workflows such as doctor, target-profile rehearsal, redacted engagement status, capture triage, campaign/envelope planning, evidence lint/pack verification, and the protocol-torture exit gate where their existing contracts support it. Use library APIs where practical and fixed argv otherwise. Return a common versioned result envelope with networkActivity=false, bounded data, warnings, errors, artifacts, timing, and sensitivity labels. Never accept arbitrary commands or options.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","tools","offline"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"l","title":"Implement typed offline MCP tool adapters"}	blake3:Tl13rVy-YNyhIbf6Da2ON3P2KoM-7IeDhyDGF7npPqQ
1784499346344927	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr4QI		item.create	bn-806	{"description":"Centralize fixed-command execution with no shell, explicit timeouts, output-size ceilings, process-group cleanup, deterministic environment, and secret redaction. Confine all caller-supplied paths beneath the configured work root using canonical containment checks and reject symlinks where required. Bound JSON nesting/collection inputs and concurrent requests. Acceptance: timeout, flood, traversal, symlink, environment injection, signal, and secret fixtures fail safely with stable structured errors and no lingering process.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","hardening"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Harden MCP execution, paths, output, and redaction"}	blake3:5IaNejKDGlTWBJt5Mh6bidCowvTOgTRvd3WSqsVn7jY
1784499346528172	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr4gI		item.create	bn-ar2	{"description":"Teach the unified launcher a dedicated MCP container mode with --network=none, no NET_RAW/NET_ADMIN/NET_BIND_SERVICE capabilities, a read-only work mount for Phase 1, and only required documentation/schema assets installed in the image. Preserve Podman-first portable runtime selection. Acceptance: normal MCP discovery/tools work in the sandbox; runtime inspection and a negative network probe prove no network namespace access or packet capabilities are available.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","container","security"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Run MCP in an offline least-privilege container mode"}	blake3:NvI0cKPSZSMq16EFLe_g1Ao6gOFTEVjp1RVTE00TYOM
1784499346706091	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr4wI		item.create	bn-xme	{"description":"Add concise setup examples for launching ./bin/sippycup mcp from common stdio-capable clients, enumerate available resources/tools, explain sensitivity and local privilege inheritance, and state what MCP intentionally cannot do. Cover optional dependency/install paths, work-root conventions, troubleshooting, protocol compatibility, and the separate authorization path for future live actions.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","docs"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"s","title":"Document MCP client setup and operator boundaries"}	blake3:HcBH2aS3a7c1LCgxq5TyO4mwJgBX2t-vcZSRJE8EH1o
1784499346891642	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr5AI		item.create	bn-l4u	{"description":"Close Phase 1 only after a network-free automated acceptance suite initializes with a real MCP client, lists/reads resources, lists/calls every allowlisted tool against fixtures, validates schemas and structured errors, checks stdout protocol purity, bounds/timeout/redaction/path behavior, graceful shutdown, and launcher portability. Prove the container has no network and no packet capabilities and record exact commands, image digest, test totals, and known limitations on the goal.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","exit-gate","security"],"parent":"bn-2oi","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: prove offline MCP interoperability and containment"}	blake3:ONwWLozsFVZKStWEKaj4LJmW45iE3VHAqptDT5CUtAw
1784499371213344	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr5QI		item.create	bn-3eb	{"description":"Design and implement a short-lived, externally issued capability artifact that binds an MCP live request to an approved target profile, literal frozen endpoints, tool/action, reviewed plan digest, caller/client identity, expiry, nonce, and hard traffic ceilings. The server may validate but never mint or broaden grants. Acceptance includes replay, expiry, tamper, path swap, DNS drift, action confusion, ceiling escalation, and fail-closed audit tests.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","authorization","security"],"parent":"bn-1hq","size":"l","title":"Define unforgeable live MCP capability grants"}	blake3:oBm-Izcn1iSX3xCfLWXAuRlIFeJ21C6nk__djp-yyC8
1784499371406710	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr5gI		item.create	bn-2x2	{"description":"Add typed tools that prepare and inspect immutable live artifacts without sending application traffic, then perform only the narrowly defined network preflight when a valid capability grant permits it. Return exact targets, traffic budgets, hashes, authorization state, and audit references. Preserve fixed argv, deadlines, redaction, and target scope checks; never accept an arbitrary scanner or command.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","preflight"],"parent":"bn-1hq","size":"m","title":"Expose reviewable live preparation and preflight tools"}	blake3:9kzaRYHypHxp_aEgre8WrkZwWm_6XzTySBXh7qGDmfw
1784499371597175	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr5wI		item.create	bn-2m2	{"description":"Implement the smallest target-active MCP operation: one reviewed call/canary scenario with bounded packets, CPS, concurrency=1, duration, capture, emergency stop, cleanup, and append-only evidence. Require a valid capability grant tied to the exact immutable plan. Revalidate immediately before side effects and return a structured receipt rather than raw secrets or unlimited logs.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","live","safety"],"parent":"bn-1hq","size":"l","title":"Expose one-call live execution with hard ceilings"}	blake3:doDDjDWBfvuMvSe_fIqQHNXZCC_YHpZP42dzoh4OTRM
1784499371786313	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr6AI		item.create	bn-3oq	{"description":"Run a controlled loopback or explicitly approved target acceptance campaign proving zero packets for absent/invalid/expired/replayed grants, exact endpoint/digest binding, ceiling enforcement, cancellation and crash cleanup, redaction, and evidence completeness. Manually inspect packet captures and journal chain, record exact transcript and known limitations, and retain external human authorization as a prerequisite rather than an MCP action.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","exit-gate","authorization"],"parent":"bn-1hq","size":"m","title":"Exit gate: prove approval-bound MCP live execution"}	blake3:MseOyIVesn04W3AqMAy79rTvXVVBL9UF1zSbgWEhl7g
1784499371973245	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr6QI		item.create	bn-13t	{"description":"Map the existing declarative campaign runner into capability-bound start, status, bounded-event-read, cancel, and evidence-receipt tools. Use server-generated run identifiers, enforce one-way state transitions and per-client quotas, preserve global and manifest ceilings, and avoid returning secret-bearing/raw payload data. No arbitrary manifest extensions or embedded shell.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","campaigns","live"],"parent":"bn-291","size":"xl","title":"Expose a supervised MCP campaign lifecycle"}	blake3:eCp4RZUsFrNnUtgQtNGURpspQ8rpZ4lRRvG17kRjZuQ
1784499372164751	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr6gI		item.create	bn-2qs	{"description":"Add bounded event buffers, pagination/cursors, output truncation markers, request concurrency limits, cancellation propagation, process-group cleanup, restart reconciliation, and orphan detection for long-running agent workflows. Acceptance: slow or disconnected clients cannot exhaust memory or leave target traffic running; cancellation and server restart converge to auditable terminal states.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","resilience"],"parent":"bn-291","size":"l","title":"Guarantee MCP cancellation, backpressure, and recovery"}	blake3:eseF2KD9SYpxx0j3nLhWFPqhwKJo_z8HpI1GD4YkaPw
1784499372365860	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr6wI		item.create	bn-3i8	{"description":"Write an ADR comparing local stdio against streamable HTTP for concrete multi-host use cases. If remote transport is not necessary, explicitly decline it. If selected, require TLS, OAuth-compatible authentication, per-client identity and authorization, origin/host validation, rate limits, revocation, audit correlation, secure secret storage, deployment guidance, and adversarial tests; never expose an unauthenticated bind.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","architecture","remote"],"parent":"bn-291","size":"m","title":"Decide whether remote MCP transport is justified","urgency":"punt"}	blake3:XU56Xu-yVGYm_qqcGcThJ6E5BJbtJC0K8jlKmWy5Mh0
1784499372560233	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr7AI		item.create	bn-2bo	{"description":"Close Phase 3 only after stress, interruption, restart, slow-client, quota, identity-isolation, replay, revocation, and evidence-integrity tests pass under realistic campaign concurrency. If remote transport ships, include authenticated interoperability and network exposure tests; otherwise record the ADR decision and test only stdio campaign supervision. Document exact limits and residual risks.","kind":"task","labels":["mcp","exit-gate","security"],"parent":"bn-291","size":"l","title":"Exit gate: prove supervised and remote MCP safety","urgency":"punt"}	blake3:tc0V4IY5TYUUP5Kkvj9yRY58wRjfo4TAFy2MUy8hO_w
