1784500581202403	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErqwM		item.comment	bn-l4u	{"body":"EXIT GATE PASS — 2026-07-19. Rebuilt localhost/sippycup:latest as image ID 284cbd5946fc372e9fc9df89e119321fb9447e782274e04b031fe50e4d5bb612. make mcp-exit-gate passed 12 focused tests plus eight real stock-client/container checks: initialize, static resource discovery/read, exact ten-tool allowlist, every tool call against fixtures, offline container containment, result-schema validation, and traversal rejection. make smoke passed with MCP SDK/entrypoint/package checks. Repository regression: 319 top-level tests, 79 oracle tests plus 20,000-packet benchmark (1.589726s/3,942,782 bytes), 33 torture, 28 TUI and 31 learned-pack tests: 490 unique tests passed. Network activity: none. Known limits: stdio/local container only; direct host mode is development-only and not network-isolated; work is read-only so tools return results rather than create artifacts; campaign MCP planning requires literal addresses and at most 1,000 steps; ten offline tools only; no journal/raw-capture resource, shell, arbitrary argv, live preflight/call/campaign/chaos/load, authorization mutation, remote transport or streaming lifecycle; SDK is pinned to v1.27.2 pending a separately tested future major-version migration."}	blake3:4CVvGjeldtRgtOsY5C7m9c-ChuGc0Gjvd5xUnNYLlGc
1784500581242851	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErrAM		item.move	bn-l4u	{"state":"done"}	blake3:9lk5hmzOvGgNSQhu-De9mpXOnotezF5xhRYTKFPbvvc
1784500581246561	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErrQM		item.move	bn-2oi	{"reason":"auto-completed: all children of bn-2oi are done","state":"done"}	blake3:uyg1Vg9BrfNwD1wFQnUKqecC5I3d6i1xhXNeBhuljNo
1784500581272681	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErrgM		item.comment	bn-2oi	{"body":"PHASE 1 EXIT GATE PASS — 2026-07-19. All seven child bones are complete. The shipped surface is local stdio, ten typed offline tools, allowlisted public resources, versioned structured results, fixed-output/time/concurrency/path bounds, explicit redaction, and an actually offline least-privilege container. Image 284cbd5946fc372e9fc9df89e119321fb9447e782274e04b031fe50e4d5bb612; 490 unique regression tests, container smoke, and the eight-check stock-client gate passed with zero target traffic. Live MCP work remains a separate blocked phase and MCP cannot grant authorization."}	blake3:HVobMaXJIFBRT4uV4fSTKRkH2iA510HK_EnQuoYW8wI
1784500651170592	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErrwM		item.update	bn-2s6	{"field":"title","value":"Add optional quality and observability profiles"}	blake3:ARzfsYIa2cgw-7iGTRGnfRHKh-mze-5OaJ-PK-Vr4xI
1784500651182284	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErsAM		item.update	bn-2s6	{"field":"description","value":"Keep heavyweight integrations outside core: ViSQOL aggregate scoring, Zeek UDP SIP cross-checking, and optional HEP/HOMER export. WebRTC now has a dedicated browser-realistic assessment goal because Quad confirmed it is in scope."}	blake3:3JiR6-N571Yxptn56Z2YDnO8eB3_jk34c8MPh3vYmrI
1784500651377406	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErsQM		item.create	bn-3c5	{"description":"Build an optional but first-class WebRTC voice assessment track spanning service-specific WSS signaling, ICE/STUN/TURN, SDP offer-answer and trickle/restart behavior, DTLS-SRTP identity and keying, browser-origin/session controls, media invariants, privacy-safe evidence, and a disposable local exit gate. Preserve Sippycup's approval, literal-target, bounded-traffic, and single-entrypoint guarantees. Quad has confirmed WebRTC coverage is useful; exact production signaling and deployment details remain approval-bound.","kind":"goal","labels":["webrtc","security","browser","media"],"parent":"bn-22t","size":"xl","title":"Add browser-realistic WebRTC security assessment coverage"}	blake3:3unSWMK7jEDZgJs9TUmBZIm9bCUCG8F0I7JcOdn9n3M
1784500682401962	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErsgM		item.create	bn-e64	{"description":"Document trust boundaries and abuse cases across browser/peer, WSS signaling, identity/session service, ICE/STUN/TURN, DTLS, SRTP/RTCP, media application, and admin plane. Define in-scope protocols, literal endpoints, credentials/roles, ceilings, privacy classes, stop conditions, and what requires Quad's explicit approval. Acceptance: a versioned model maps every later check to an asset, attacker capability, evidence source, and safe execution class.","kind":"task","labels":["threat-model","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"m","title":"Model WebRTC attack surfaces and authorization boundaries"}	blake3:HyWXU24T-jlrCbdbso5ijJhWoImkyOGRii2_dTFLBZI
1784500682606008	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErswM		item.create	bn-gno	{"description":"Specify portable JSON schemas for peer configuration, signaling adapter capabilities, offer/answer and trickle events, ICE candidate pairs and restarts, DTLS/SRTP observations, media assertions, typed unknowns, redaction, and stable exit codes. Keep signaling transport pluggable because WebRTC does not standardize it. Acceptance: fixtures validate offline, incompatible adapter capabilities fail closed, and secrets never appear in reports or argv.","kind":"task","labels":["schema","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Define a versioned WebRTC scenario and result contract"}	blake3:butEumppJYCqbod4IpCtrgPwV8WTDP8uQZLhC5PgtN8
1784500682812697	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErtAM		item.create	bn-23q	{"description":"Add a pinned, reproducible optional peer built on an independent WebRTC implementation such as Pion, available through bin/sippycup without bloating core. Support audio-only offer/answer, trickle ICE, ICE restart, STUN/TURN UDP/TCP/TLS as available, DTLS-SRTP, RTCP, deterministic canary audio, bounded duration/traffic, and stable JSON events. Include network-free fixtures and provenance.","kind":"task","labels":["pion","container","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Package an independent WebRTC peer profile"}	blake3:FjB9Usnn7a2vhkAwOIm6Q0z-S26hKjxE8ONTNRn13Ec
1784500683016514	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErtQM		item.create	bn-3cr	{"description":"Define and implement a narrow service-specific signaling adapter plus authorized checks for TLS validation, Origin enforcement, cross-site WebSocket hijacking, authentication and expiry, replay, message authorization, size/rate ceilings, malformed state transitions, and clean disconnect/reconnect. No generic arbitrary WebSocket or admin request primitive. Coordinate shared auth coverage with bn-1xm.","kind":"task","labels":["websocket","signaling","auth"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Build pluggable WSS signaling and browser-session probes"}	blake3:9xW46QAEWNCKfTm0sMdOYG52-qHWH89KZexLs63DcCw
1784500683220059	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErtgM		item.create	bn-28z	{"description":"Assess candidate policy and disclosure, connectivity checks, nomination, consent freshness, ICE restart, mDNS/host/server-reflexive/relay behavior, TURN credential lifetime, allocation permissions, channel binding, transport fallback, amplification exposure, and recovery. Distinguish peer, server, and network failures; impose literal-server and packet/time ceilings.","kind":"task","labels":["ice","stun","turn"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Implement ICE, STUN, and TURN security oracles"}	blake3:jgpKy0bAU4skpCCt5QmnuBma6ruqAfl6A2ESngVfUyw
1784500683430317	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErtwM		item.create	bn-22j	{"description":"Parse and validate WebRTC SDP revisions: BUNDLE groups, mids, rtcp-mux, ICE credentials/options, trickle/end-of-candidates, fingerprints/setup roles, codecs/rtcp-fb/extmaps, direction changes, glare, rollback, renegotiation, and ICE restarts. Generate bounded negative/pairwise cases and minimize failures without assuming SIP semantics.","kind":"task","labels":["sdp","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Implement SDP offer-answer and negotiation oracles"}	blake3:8HzhbdYJ5jvP0TrucwI-RhkQFVeET7AUK-EYu3Vev1I
1784500683646147	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEruAM		item.create	bn-1k1	{"description":"Verify certificate fingerprint binding, DTLS role negotiation, version/cipher policy observations, downgrade resistance, SRTP profile selection, replay handling, SSRC/sequence behavior, RTCP protection, key separation, rekey/restart behavior, and failure closure. Report observable evidence conservatively without attempting to expose session keys.","kind":"task","labels":["dtls","srtp","security"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Implement DTLS-SRTP identity and media-security oracles"}	blake3:1qz9U9VQ3NESABoCGy7rfMdcecqpOnojbYR-CaKYXmI
1784500683862258	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEruQM		item.create	bn-2r3	{"description":"Correlate signaling revisions, ICE pair changes, DTLS association, SRTP/RTCP streams, deterministic audio canaries, continuity/latency, and recovery into one call verdict. Redact ICE credentials, tokens, candidate addresses where policy requires, and browser/device metadata; retain explicit uncertainty for encrypted or partial captures.","kind":"task","labels":["media","evidence","privacy"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Extend media and evidence analysis for WebRTC calls"}	blake3:QkJRYtl1pYolbcJJUM4EIG9iOpdsCQegxgeaCEMk-78
1784500684074013	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErugM		item.create	bn-sou	{"description":"Expose profile install/status, offline validation, local lab, authorized one-call execution, capture/triage, and evidence/report commands through bin/sippycup. Doctor must explain optional dependencies and actionable installation; documentation must provide a newcomer-safe happy path and failure recovery without suggesting production scanning.","kind":"task","labels":["cli","ux","docs"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"m","title":"Integrate WebRTC workflows into the single Sippycup entrypoint"}	blake3:b_IvQOnBv4RqRVsgvwBpbjTjxWvd_vrvzs3CgPmWQYE
1784500684295600	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEruwM		item.create	bn-3j8	{"description":"Run a disposable local topology with at least two independent endpoints and, where relevant, local signaling plus coturn. Prove offer/answer, trickle, direct and relay paths, ICE restart, DTLS-SRTP audio/RTCP, seeded failures, cancellation, recovery, evidence redaction, hard ceilings, and zero unintended egress. Require all functionality to be reachable from bin/sippycup and publish exact limits and residual gaps.","kind":"task","labels":["exit-gate","integration","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Exit gate browser-realistic WebRTC safety and interoperability"}	blake3:Pxm4JZ5g3SrLkwLdyw6O5nbcwOTjIgYRqYrcSdSgyZQ
