1784501085851605	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr0QM		item.comment	bn-e64	{"body":"Completed the WebRTC threat-model contract in docs/WEBRTC-THREAT-MODEL.md. It defines ten protected asset classes, six explicit attacker capabilities, separate browser/signaling/identity/ICE-TURN/DTLS-SRTP/media/evidence/admin boundaries, evidence-backed invariants, data classification, offline/local/approved-target execution classes, authorization requirements, fail-closed stop conditions, component responsibilities, and eight live admission criteria. It explicitly treats discovered candidates as observations rather than authorization, keeps signaling service-specific, separates admin and load scope, and forbids secret/key material in normal evidence. Linked from OPTIONAL-PROFILES.md. No target traffic occurred."}	blake3:QHEdWsa-xeJZEPFA60BL68rLc9hclOzOCuhTTH18OQg
