1784502293636841	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr2QM		item.comment	bn-23q	{"body":"Completed the optional independent WebRTC peer profile. Added a separate digest-pinned Go/Pion v4.2.13 build, locked go.mod/go.sum graph, exact source-input digest and repository revision provenance, optional image labels, and the unified commands './bin/sippycup webrtc build|status|capabilities|self-test'. The fixed sandbox uses --network=none, cap-drop ALL, read-only root, no-new-privileges, PID limit 128, and a 16 MiB noexec tmpfs. The loopback self-test registers only PCMU audio, exchanges trickle ICE candidates, establishes DTLS-SRTP, sends exactly 50 deterministic 20 ms packets/8000 payload bytes, verifies digest 7390f38421a29be2eb3d217b6d3886bb478acaff3228c9a4271c0e85221be836, observes RTCP, performs a real ICE restart, gracefully closes both peers, and waits for the RTCP reader. Stable capability/self-test schemas distinguish available STUN/TURN support from locally verified audio/trickle/restart/DTLS-SRTP/RTCP. Events contain hashes/classes/counters only: no SDP, candidate addresses, ICE credentials, keys, or payloads. Validation: Go unit, vet, and race tests; 14 WebRTC contract tests; 19 unified CLI tests; 334 core regression tests; schema validation under pinned jsonschema; core smoke; 8-check MCP containment gate; repeated native/container self-tests. Core image b66bc2554399d8bf765e9bd120e7a2659175fca63e6224fafdf2571614d10fdd; optional image 30559afb9f1c096a04cc49053e9b4ebea6b6e8f6da860a3e751b17348035914f. No assessment target traffic occurred; only build dependency downloads and loopback self-tests."}	blake3:5olUzztJP9fn7VyQjIOiN70XBHISHG4fC2lHYqgLugg
