1784514384797414	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr9QM		item.comment	bn-sou	{"body":"Milestones 387e511 and the guided-workflow commit add unified offline scenario/result validation with optional concrete capability binding, doctor install/status/verification guidance, newcomer-safe workflow/recovery documentation, MCP discovery, and unified local audio/WSS lab commands. All local execution remains loopback confined. Focused validation: 61 WebRTC tests plus Go tests/vet; 57 CLI/workbench/MCP tests. Remaining for this bone is the service-specific authorization-bound one-call target action, which cannot be implemented honestly until Quad supplies the signaling protocol and approved staging scope."}	blake3:eOFw6bPiLKq3JwlgOCpFlUUWwHxqUHpUNr48UaI7YbA
1784514447066778	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAEr9gM		item.create	bn-3vu	{"description":"Implement the target-facing one-call action only after the service owner supplies the fixed signaling protocol, literal staging destinations, TLS identities, external credential roles, allowed Origins, written approval reference/window, permitted negative checks, and hard call/message/packet/byte ceilings. Revalidate authorization and destination bindings at execution time; expose no arbitrary WSS/HTTP primitive; capture, cancel, clean up, and emit privacy-safe normalized evidence. This Bone preserves the live portion split from bn-sou so the local interoperability exit gate is not blocked on external protocol details.","kind":"task","labels":["authorization","live","webrtc"],"parent":"bn-3c5","size":"l","title":"Add approval-bound service-specific WebRTC one-call execution"}	blake3:1mNKpa4ybt5UTaASReWqr77zxF9PbEJvZ3DVzuWpFkg
