1784557469246258	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErjAQ		item.assign	bn-2m2	{"action":"assign","agent":"bob-dev"}	blake3:knTKrRj5MPt62Zv3v1lpF4dg5FnzjaEWKRBZConHjEU
1784557469262066	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErjQQ		item.comment	bn-2m2	{"body":"Implementation started after bn-2x2. Work is limited to local/fake/loopback validation until explicit target approval and bn-3oq; no external traffic will be sent."}	blake3:owTvIcB1TZS3NlwZ1Xe-Z5PjZigqUofanFAcZId_MtY
1784558043970491	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErjgQ		item.comment	bn-2m2	{"body":"Implemented opt-in execute_one_call MCP tool and fixed helper. It descriptor-pins grant/profile/plan/manifest, verifies the manifest-plan lock, rejects credentials and any plan other than one call with calls/CPS/concurrency=1, applies local maxima (60s, 2,000 packets, 2 MiB, 200 pps), binds signaling plus exact media port range, atomically consumes the grant, rechecks expiry, then delegates to the existing capture/watchdog/process-group cleanup/payload-strip/report/evidence pipeline. Results are bounded hash-only receipts. The tool is disabled by default behind SIPPYCUP_MCP_LIVE_ENABLE_ONE_CALL=1 pending bn-3oq; enabling adds NET_RAW only inside the bridge, never NET_ADMIN. The fixed helper has a 130s outer deadline with graceful SIGTERM cleanup then SIGKILL fallback; container termination is the emergency stop. Validation: MCP 34/34, CLI 26/26, full discovery 430/430, final image build/smoke pass, offline MCP interoperability gate pass. No external target traffic was sent."}	blake3:b2LsIWxtPzik2YFBZAPwEp-wt1xDuAm0eD91WtQkZjs
1784558043990744	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErjwQ		item.move	bn-2m2	{"state":"done"}	blake3:OC8Q8nSSSx4oQVjPfXhw2P8wtVfN3uvmQ8AdciksSXM
1784558115511495	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErkAQ		item.comment	bn-3oq	{"body":"Local implementation prerequisites are now complete: bn-3eb, bn-2x2, and bn-2m2 are closed in commits feadf59, 764ed2b, and 4e669a5. The one-call tool remains disabled by default. This exit gate is now blocked on bn-guh: Quad's written approval, literal staging endpoints, validity window, and controlled live evidence review. No external target traffic has been sent."}	blake3:M2uMRLXK-PTWlmu-U26cqNS8IYyGg10_mUNsIqcBp2A
1784558115531524	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErkQQ		item.comment	bn-1hq	{"body":"Phase 2 implementation chain is complete through the feature-gated one-call tool. Remaining acceptance is bn-3oq, which is intentionally blocked by bn-guh pending Quad's written staging authorization and live evidence inspection."}	blake3:RE9bdvfJq7K-E2L4Y9KVYZYdhxI4Xqvb3RdIdPKbDhU
1784558115549587	bob-dev	itc:v3:AWKc55JPnzzNAAAAAAAAQbu9V997YAAAAAErkgQ		item.comment	bn-mry	{"body":"Offline MCP, signed capability verification, immutable preparation, bounded preflight, and feature-gated one-call execution are implemented. The remaining non-punt MCP path is intentionally held at the approval-bound live exit gate (bn-guh -> bn-3oq); later supervised campaign/cancellation tasks depend on that gate."}	blake3:s68jKg9J80-GUDFWJj-SJ5NveJ71Z2J4c4SybzE8OkU
